description: I have a difficult relationship with Moscow. But it so happens that I live here. By itself, this city does not touch me, does not speak to me. But there are artists who make the city speak. One of these artists is Kirill Kto. He has carved eyes on the grids of restored buildings throughout the city for years. I love this project. And I love it when city services sew up the eyes with patches, the eyes remain, and the threads look like eyelashes.
